Brilliance is fleeting. 11-Jul-21 05:21 PM
The music lab. Walking in, it's a rather wide room. You can see the acoustic foam squares surrounding the walls of the room. The back of the room is completely occupied by steps. It seems this is the place musicians would stand while playing their instrument. To the right of you when you walk in is a place where instruments are stored. To the left is a small recording booth, separated by glass walls from the rest of the room. There are about 4 steps leading up. They're quite wide and seem to be made out of plastic. The steps are large enough so that a row of people could stand on them as well as enough room for a music stand. You're also able to fold up the steps, but that takes more than one person to do, or someone of incredible strength. Towards the right, there's a multitude of lockers where people store their instruments. However, for your usage, all of them have been unlocked. There's just about every type of instrument here, from the common trumpet, to the large and obscure hyperbass flute. There's also a little area for instrument maintenance, holding items such as valve oil and spare reeds. There's also a recording booth for you to use. There's a high quality mic in there, and it can record just about anything. If you set the sensitivity high enough, it's able to record just about anything in this room. You won't be able to take it with you though. There's a small monitor in here that lets you edit and warp the audio, as well as play it back.
